<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-09-01T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-09-01T00:00:00-05:00" n="368" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d368">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 763.72112/119</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Great Britain</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_PWH1" type="from"><hi rend="italic">Page</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi><note n="1" xml:id="d368fn1">Transmitted to the Ambassadors in
                                Germany and Austria-Hungary, September 2.</note>
                        </head>
                        <dateline>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Embassy</hi>, <lb/>
                            <placeName>
                                <hi rend="italic">London</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-09-01">
                                <hi rend="italic">September 1, 1914</hi>.</date>
                            <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received 5:30 p.m.</hi>] </dateline>
                        <p rend="center">[Telegram]</p>
                        <p>547. With reference to the attitude of the Austro-Hungarian and German
                            Governments regarding the Declaration of London, the British Government
                            ask that further inquiry be made as to whether the two Governments in
                            question have specified the articles which they intend to treat as
                            contraband of war.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">American Ambassador</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>